Quote:I am curious about having it register via the dns/dhcp server, is that do-able in Windows 2003 without things being on an AD?Why would you want to? If you have an MPLS network, everyone can talk to your AD and DDNS servers. Easy peazy. Trying to do DDNS without AD in Windows is probably more difficult since you have to dis-integrate them. I'm sure more than one horror story here has been attributed to such inanity.
