andyfatbastard wrote:They don't really get sarcasm. I'm genuinely not sure if they are too stupid to know they are being patronised, or too polite to show annoyance when it happens.I wonder this myself many days. Often I am polite to a fault.Them: RTFM.Me: That was my first attempt. However, the manual was poorly written. It uses a rather obfuscated approach.Them: Or maybe you suck at reading it.Me: I appreciate your direct candor. Here is what the manual states [long description, result of tests]. That didn't work.Them: They obviously that's not the right command, is it?Me: That was also occurred to me, so I am glad we are on the same page. What do you suggest?Them: I suggest you read the goddamn manual and find out.Me: I was not aware you didn't know, either. But perhaps you can point me in a better direction, or maybe know someone who is more versed in this than we are? Who do you go to for guidance?Them: I read the goddamned manual. You are wasting my time.Me: Then I shall be brief. There are suggestions in this department that you are the expert on these things, and I shall correct that so nobody bothers you again. I will contact your management and see who they suggest, and cc you for your future needs. That will be the last time I contact you. Thank you for your time.Them: Fuck off.Me: I am flattered, but I am married.
