So today I got my fun phone call from my ops desk (small office, so IT is one of my hats.)"Hey, I was on my google home page, went to a top stories link, and then I got an antivirus popup. Can you do something here before I click on anything?"I dragged myself over, looked at the popup, and it was a standard IE popup, asking to run a scan for "Windows Antivirus 2012."I nuked the process, grabbed hijackthis off the corptech software share, ran it, made sure the default settings were intact, then restarted IE. Then added the last visited website to a blacklist. Huzzah for users that think before clicking!
